            <fr:title text="Cardinality of the set of partial functions">Cardinality of the set of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00K7.xml" title="Partial function" addr="jms-00K7" type="local">partial functions</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>For all finite sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathord {\#}{\mathopen {}\left (A\mathbin {\rightharpoonup } B\right )\mathclose {}}={\mathopen {}\left (\mathord {\#}{B}+1\right )\mathclose {}}^{\mathord {\#}{A}}]]></fr:tex>, recalling that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathord {\#}{S}]]></fr:tex> is the cardinality of a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
